# CSS and Styling Rules

## Color Scheme
- **NO BLUE COLORS** - User specifically requested no blue shades
- Use orange/amber as primary colors (primary-500: #ed7519)
- Use green as secondary colors (secondary-500: #22c55e)
- Use purple/pink as accent colors (accent-500: #d946ef)
- Use neutral grays for text and backgrounds

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- Use Tailwind utility classes as primary styling method
- Create custom components for repeated patterns
- Use @apply directive sparingly and only for complex components
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind breakpoints

## Dark Mode
- Implement dark mode support for all components
- Use separate light and dark styles to avoid interference
- Test both modes thoroughly
- Use CSS custom properties for theme switching

## Typography
- Use Inter font family as primary font
- Implement proper font weights (300, 400, 500, 600, 700)
- Use consistent text sizing and spacing
- Ensure proper contrast ratios for accessibility

## Layout
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts
- Implement proper spacing with Tailwind spacing scale
- Use consistent border radius (rounded-lg: 8px)
- Implement proper shadows and depth

## Accessibility
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement focus states for interactive elements
- Test with screen readers

## Component Styling
- Create reusable button styles (.btn-primary, .btn-secondary, .btn-outline)
- Implement consistent form styling (.input-field)
- Use card components for content containers (.card)
- Maintain consistent spacing and padding
